commentTextItems.html: dstraying down the leg side, full on his pads, just flicks it and helps it on its way and the ball just races fine to the ropes as India win this match in style

commentPostTextItems.html: India level the series here at Hyderabad 2-2 with this magnificient win
The final ODI at Guwahati becomes the decider now
The Indians have done really well to level the series, infact at one stage after losing early wickets, India looked like losing the series here today
But the youngsters had other ideas - Kaif's solidity and Yuvraj's blitzkrieg got the match for India
Yuvraj was ruthless and hammered 80* off just 60 balls with 8 fours and one six
This sets up an exciting final ODI...dont forget to get back to us for the LIVE commentary of that match on 19th March, 2002
Remember, its a day match and starts at 0900 hrs IST (0330 hrs. GMT) on tuesday
Also your comments and suggestions are welcome to comms@cricinfo.com, as usual
Thats it for now from the CricInfo team ... Bye bye... Good Night!

Dont forget to visit http://www.cricinfo.com/link_to_database/ARCHIVE/2001-02/ZIM_IN_IND/ for all the details about this Zimbabwe tour of India - You have a lot of interesting features, statistics, photographs, polls and contests - Don't Miss it!

commentTextItems.html: on off stump, leans forward and defends it to mid on
taps it off his pads to short fine leg for the single, just 2 more needed now to level the series
gets his front foot forward and takes it as a low full toss and flicks it wide of mid wicket and the placement and timing was perfect that the ball wouldnt stop unless it hits a boundary board
pitched up, punches it back past the bowler towards long off and gets 2 more quick runs
gets well forward and flicks it past the mid wicket fielder and gets a couple of runs quickly
low full toss, leans forward and guides it down to third man for the easy single to get back on strike
